WEBVTT

00:15.473 --> 00:17.475
[indistinct chatter in background]

00:20.729 --> 00:22.022
[Luther grunts]

00:22.105 --> 00:23.189
[bell dings]

00:23.690 --> 00:25.400
[phone ringing]

00:27.902 --> 00:30.071
[Luther exhales]

00:30.155 --> 00:31.322
Good mornin'!

00:31.990 --> 00:33.700
-[phone rings]
-For some.

00:34.868 --> 00:35.869
Huh.

00:35.952 --> 00:38.455
["The Passenger" by Iggy Pop playing]

00:38.538 --> 00:40.415
[exhales sharply, grunts]

00:51.968 --> 00:54.137
[raven cawing]

00:57.682 --> 00:59.768
♪ I am the passenger ♪

01:00.435 --> 01:02.937
-[Luther] Morning!
-♪ And I ride, and I ride ♪

01:03.021 --> 01:04.314
[raven squawking]

01:04.814 --> 01:08.026
♪ I ride through the city's backsides ♪

01:08.109 --> 01:11.237
-[cawing]
-♪ I see the stars come out of the sky ♪

01:12.072 --> 01:14.783
♪ Yeah they're bright in a hollow sky ♪

01:14.866 --> 01:18.620
-[rapid grunts]
-♪ You know it looks so good tonight ♪

01:18.703 --> 01:19.704
[sighs]

01:21.164 --> 01:22.040
[Luther] Huh.

01:26.294 --> 01:28.296
♪ I am the passenger… ♪

01:28.379 --> 01:30.048
[ominous music playing]

01:30.131 --> 01:32.342
[ravens cawing]

01:32.425 --> 01:34.761
[cawing, wings fluttering]

01:34.844 --> 01:36.805
Oh shit.

01:37.972 --> 01:39.307
Shit!

01:39.390 --> 01:40.975
Whoa!

01:41.059 --> 01:43.103
[cawing]

01:43.186 --> 01:44.270
Whoa!

01:46.523 --> 01:48.691
[frightened whimpering]

01:48.775 --> 01:49.609
[grunts]

01:52.403 --> 01:53.363
[Luther groans]

01:53.446 --> 01:56.407
[ravens squawking]

01:56.491 --> 01:58.785
-[energy pulsing]
-Oh… Whoa!

01:59.410 --> 02:00.537
Oh shit!

02:03.748 --> 02:04.833
Hello there, stranger.

02:04.916 --> 02:06.918
[dramatic orchestral music playing]

02:09.963 --> 02:11.840
Oh! Hey.

02:17.637 --> 02:19.472
[ravens cawing]

02:25.979 --> 02:28.523
[thunder rumbling]

02:29.190 --> 02:31.943
[somber orchestral music playing]

02:32.610 --> 02:34.696
This one, or this one?

02:34.779 --> 02:37.949
Uh-uh. I wanna hear about the time

02:38.032 --> 02:41.119
the Umbrella Academy
defeated the robbers at the museum.

02:41.202 --> 02:42.662
[Allison] Again?

02:43.371 --> 02:45.290
Okay. [laughs softly]

02:46.457 --> 02:49.711
It was a dark and stormy night…

02:51.796 --> 02:52.922
[gasps]

02:53.548 --> 02:55.758
[excited breaths]

03:03.600 --> 03:05.768
Claire, it's Mommy.

03:05.852 --> 03:07.604
-Mommy?
-[gasps]

03:07.687 --> 03:08.688
[screaming]

03:09.272 --> 03:10.148
What?

03:10.857 --> 03:12.567
-Who the hell are you?
-Patrick? Wh--

03:12.650 --> 03:15.862
-Mommy! Mommy!
-What's going on? Who is this woman?

03:15.945 --> 03:17.197
Wh-- Where's my baby?

03:17.280 --> 03:18.698
You have ten seconds to leave.

03:18.781 --> 03:21.284
-Where is Claire?!
-Lady, there's no Claire here.

03:21.367 --> 03:23.411
-You're scaring her!
-I'm sorry. I…

03:25.079 --> 03:26.831
[shuddering breaths]

03:27.457 --> 03:28.750
Something is wrong.

03:32.212 --> 03:33.838
Something is very wrong.

03:34.505 --> 03:36.507
-[thunderclap]
-[man clears throat]

03:36.591 --> 03:38.301
[man] We're here. Hotel Obsidian.

03:48.770 --> 03:50.772
[phone ringing]

04:01.491 --> 04:04.869
[pensive instrumental music playing]

04:07.247 --> 04:09.249
We take all kinds here.

04:36.567 --> 04:38.069
[Sissy] You have given me

04:39.070 --> 04:41.447
the greatest gift of a lifetime.

04:42.073 --> 04:45.326
You let me feel alive for the first time.

04:46.577 --> 04:47.620
[weeping]

04:47.704 --> 04:49.622
You helped me find hope again.

04:50.707 --> 04:52.375
That's a wonderful thing.

04:52.959 --> 04:55.878
[emotional string music playing]

05:17.483 --> 05:20.278
[Sissy] You don't even notice
the box that you're in

05:20.820 --> 05:23.406
until someone comes along
and lets you out.

05:37.795 --> 05:39.380
-[barber] Can I help you?
-Hey.

05:43.885 --> 05:44.844
Thanks.

05:53.728 --> 05:54.729
[groans]

05:56.981 --> 05:58.983
-[squeals]
-[playful instrumental music playing]

05:59.067 --> 06:00.109
[exhales sharply]

06:01.361 --> 06:02.653
[Diego snoring]

06:11.287 --> 06:13.289
[Diego continues snoring softly]

06:20.922 --> 06:24.675
[Klaus] Old Holland Road, Pennsylvania.

06:24.759 --> 06:26.552
-Hmm.
-[Diego sighs]

06:26.636 --> 06:28.930
[snoring softly]

06:31.140 --> 06:34.811
[light jazz music playing]

06:38.773 --> 06:42.068
[phone ringing]

06:52.495 --> 06:54.122
Christ, what a dump.

06:56.499 --> 06:59.252
That little delinquent is your son?

06:59.335 --> 07:02.588
-Allegedly my son.
-[laughs] That's so funny!

07:05.508 --> 07:07.385
Wait, who's… who's the mother?

07:07.468 --> 07:09.053
-Lila.
-Excuse me?

07:09.137 --> 07:10.763
-Whoa, Lila's here?
-[Diego] Was.

07:10.847 --> 07:13.099
She dropped him off in my lap
last night then bolted.

07:13.182 --> 07:15.309
-I don't much care for that one.
-Don't.

07:15.393 --> 07:16.853
Technically, she's family.

07:16.936 --> 07:19.188
She was trying to murder us,
like, yesterday.

07:19.272 --> 07:22.733
Yeah, like I said, "family."
Diego, is she coming back?

07:22.817 --> 07:24.235
Well, she goddamn better be

07:24.318 --> 07:27.405
because we got more important things
to be dealing with right now!

07:27.488 --> 07:28.614
[Klaus] Calm down. Shh.

07:32.076 --> 07:35.288
-Where's Luther?
-Who cares? Probably out for… a run.

07:35.371 --> 07:36.622
[Klaus] Mmm!

07:36.706 --> 07:38.499
Love the haircut.

07:42.378 --> 07:44.839
So I, uh, talked to Marcus last night.

07:44.922 --> 07:46.674
Wait, what? You talked with the enemy?

07:46.757 --> 07:48.843
-[Diego] By yourself?
-Somebody had to do something.

07:48.926 --> 07:50.470
Who elected you, Vanya?

07:52.263 --> 07:53.681
It's, uh, Viktor.

07:54.974 --> 07:55.933
Who's Viktor?

07:56.767 --> 07:59.061
[dramatic music playing]

08:00.897 --> 08:01.772
I am.

08:02.273 --> 08:03.608
It's who I've always been.

08:11.240 --> 08:13.367
-Uh, is that an issue for anyone?
-[Klaus chuckles]

08:13.451 --> 08:15.036
Nah, I'm good with it.

08:15.119 --> 08:17.205
Yeah, me too. Cool.

08:18.206 --> 08:19.874
Truly happy for you, Viktor.

08:20.583 --> 08:23.127
But last time I checked,
you don't speak for this family.

08:23.211 --> 08:25.838
Okay, well, it's fine, okay?
Marcus totally gets it.

08:25.922 --> 08:28.049
He doesn't want a war any more than we do.

08:28.132 --> 08:30.468
What are you talking about?
He tried to homicide us!

08:30.551 --> 08:33.054
-So did Lila, and you had a kid with her.
-That's not the point!

08:33.137 --> 08:34.096
[Viktor] We made a deal.

08:34.180 --> 08:37.767
He's gonna give back Five's briefcase,
then we're gonna get out of the timeline.

08:37.850 --> 08:39.977
We're gonna meet later today
for the, uh, the handover.

08:40.061 --> 08:40.895
Oh, thank God!

08:40.978 --> 08:43.272
That's a rookie move. Dude is playing you.

08:43.356 --> 08:45.566
-Oh, really?
-[Diego] Yeah, but maybe we can use this.

08:45.650 --> 08:48.611
And we turn it back on them,
and then we wipe them the hell out.

08:48.694 --> 08:50.071
Diego, stop, please.

08:50.154 --> 08:52.782
And you're not gonna,
like, do anything today.

08:52.865 --> 08:55.034
Except bond with your spawn.

08:56.077 --> 08:57.453
Alleged spawn.

08:57.537 --> 08:58.996
[Viktor] I will get the briefcase,

08:59.080 --> 09:01.666
and then we will all go back
and fix the timeline.

09:01.749 --> 09:05.002
Hey, we're not going anywhere!
This is a perfectly acceptable timeline.

09:05.086 --> 09:08.714
Yeah, why don't you tell that to Allison,
who's upstairs grieving her daughter,

09:08.798 --> 09:09.966
who doesn't even exist here!

09:10.049 --> 09:11.425
Not to mention, we've been replaced

09:11.509 --> 09:13.970
by a bunch of blobs
and cubes and birds and shit!

09:14.053 --> 09:17.181
News flash, geniuses! It's not about us!

09:17.265 --> 09:18.432
Take a look around.

09:18.516 --> 09:20.977
If you hadn't noticed,
there's no doomsday.

09:21.060 --> 09:23.604
There's no apocalypse. The sun is shining.

09:23.688 --> 09:25.982
Birds are doing
whatever the hell birds do.

09:26.065 --> 09:29.026
That's all that matters.
We're done messing with time.

09:29.860 --> 09:32.280
And I'm officially retired.

09:32.363 --> 09:33.614
[sniffing]

09:35.575 --> 09:37.368
Is he wearing aftershave?

09:38.494 --> 09:39.704
I'm concerned.

09:39.787 --> 09:40.788
[energy thrumming]

09:40.871 --> 09:43.499
[shockwave pulsing]

09:45.918 --> 09:47.795
[distant screaming]

09:56.304 --> 09:59.515
Hey. What do you say
we get outta here, huh?

09:59.599 --> 10:01.976
Take a little… road trip.

10:02.893 --> 10:04.061
What are you talking about?

10:04.145 --> 10:06.856
I'm talking about
a sojourn to the countryside.

10:06.939 --> 10:09.775
You and me, the wind in our hair.

10:09.859 --> 10:12.278
Thelma and Louise on the open road.

10:12.361 --> 10:13.863
You know they die in the end, right?

10:13.946 --> 10:15.531
Holding hands,

10:15.615 --> 10:19.368
living our best life, my little cherub!

10:19.869 --> 10:20.911
[quietly] Listen to me.

10:21.412 --> 10:25.041
I nearly died
from Luther's sleep farts last night.

10:25.124 --> 10:27.418
We need to get out of here,
get some fresh air!

10:27.501 --> 10:29.462
Okay, I'll bite. Why me, Klaus?

10:29.545 --> 10:31.964
Because you said… you said you're retired,

10:32.048 --> 10:34.175
and that's what retired people do.

10:34.258 --> 10:35.760
[Klaus] And don't you deserve some fun?

10:35.843 --> 10:37.678
-[Five] There's no lobsters.
-[Klaus] Excuse me?

10:37.762 --> 10:39.889
There were three lobsters
in that tank a minute ago.

10:39.972 --> 10:43.601
Yeah, well, you know, maybe Chet
blended 'em into a morning smoothie.

10:46.312 --> 10:49.398
-You're an idiot, but I'm in.
-Whoo!

10:49.482 --> 10:51.942
-[Stan] Let me go! Get your hands off me!
-I saw what you did!

10:52.026 --> 10:53.611
Hey, what the hell are you doing?

10:53.694 --> 10:56.697
Your son stuffed
three mini muffins down his pants.

10:56.781 --> 11:00.159
And this is a buffet!
I can take whatever the hell I want!

11:00.951 --> 11:02.244
I got him. Come on.

11:02.328 --> 11:04.789
-[Stan] Wait, take it easy.
-[Diego] Time for some ground rules.

11:04.872 --> 11:06.332
How about no physical assault?

11:06.415 --> 11:08.834
-That's a--
-Shut up and listen.

11:08.918 --> 11:12.838
-[phone ringing in background]
-[distant siren wailing]

11:14.507 --> 11:16.258
My father was a Hall of Fame asshole.

11:17.593 --> 11:20.721
And when I was a little pissant like you,
I made a promise to myself

11:20.805 --> 11:24.433
that I would never act like him
to any kid of… mine.

11:24.517 --> 11:26.268
Yeah, stop. I'm gonna cry.

11:26.352 --> 11:29.689
But I'm a busy man,
with a lot on my shoulders, okay?

11:29.772 --> 11:32.566
So I'm not gonna let you
slow me down either, all right?

11:32.650 --> 11:34.735
Yeah, you look really busy right now.

11:35.403 --> 11:38.823
You can stay
until your mom gets back, all right?

11:38.906 --> 11:41.075
But no more doing dumb shit,

11:41.158 --> 11:43.619
or else you and I
are gonna have a serious problem.

11:43.703 --> 11:44.662
Look at me.

11:46.205 --> 11:47.289
¿Me entiendes?

11:48.791 --> 11:51.502
[playful instrumental music playing]

11:51.585 --> 11:52.586
Dude, your

11:53.379 --> 11:54.755
ear's leaking.

11:55.506 --> 11:57.007
Oh, I…

11:57.091 --> 12:00.094
Yeah, I forgot to pack my ear medicine.

12:00.177 --> 12:02.596
Oh sh-- Ear medicine, huh?

12:02.680 --> 12:06.892
If I don't drain it, uh, pus leaks out,
and it smells like cat puke.

12:08.227 --> 12:09.270
Come on.

12:12.815 --> 12:14.775
Whoa, whoa!
Where do you think you're going?

12:14.859 --> 12:16.318
Kid thing. I'll be right back.

12:16.402 --> 12:17.695
No. I need you to stay put

12:17.778 --> 12:19.822
and not do anything stupid
until I get the briefcase.

12:19.905 --> 12:22.032
Yeah, and you're not
the boss of him, okay?

12:24.201 --> 12:25.536
-Who--
-[Klaus] Come on.

12:25.619 --> 12:27.580
We'll get a few road sodas
for the journey.

12:27.663 --> 12:30.750
-Sometimes, you gotta clear the head out.
-[Viktor] Guys, wait. Where are you going?

12:30.833 --> 12:33.669
-Get the rats out of the maze, you know?
-[Five] Come on.

12:38.716 --> 12:43.179
[woman humming gently]

12:45.473 --> 12:46.432
Mom?

12:46.515 --> 12:48.684
Why do people keep calling me that?

12:48.768 --> 12:50.936
[groans] Where am I?

12:51.020 --> 12:53.939
The Academy, silly.
Everybody's waiting for you.

12:54.023 --> 12:55.232
[mysterious string music plays]

12:55.316 --> 12:56.525
The Academy?

12:56.609 --> 12:59.820
[humming]

12:59.904 --> 13:02.198
[indistinct chatter in background]

13:02.281 --> 13:04.658
[blender whirring]

13:04.742 --> 13:06.577
[woman laughing in background]

13:15.336 --> 13:17.630
-Ah, there he is.
-[blender stops whirring]

13:18.214 --> 13:19.840
Please, join us.

13:21.383 --> 13:23.886
It's okay. Nobody's gonna hurt you.

13:23.969 --> 13:25.513
-Smoothie?
-Oh.

13:26.847 --> 13:28.557
Yeah, thanks. [chuckles]

13:30.017 --> 13:31.560
[Fei] You must be starving.

13:32.102 --> 13:33.354
[Luther] Oh, uh…

13:33.437 --> 13:36.941
No, I… I probably shouldn't.
Is that cashew butter?

13:37.024 --> 13:40.945
Cashew butter, almond butter,
sunflower butter, tahini, Brazil nut.

13:41.445 --> 13:42.822
Wow. You know what?

13:42.905 --> 13:45.407
Now that you mention it,
I am feeling a little bit, uh,

13:45.491 --> 13:47.117
peckish, actually.

13:47.201 --> 13:48.494
-Help yourself.
-[Luther] Thanks.

13:48.577 --> 13:51.080
[playful string music playing]

13:52.122 --> 13:52.957
[softly] Wow.

13:55.709 --> 13:56.585
[exhales]

14:02.842 --> 14:05.010
So, we know you're Number One,

14:05.094 --> 14:07.638
but we haven't been
formally introduced yet.

14:07.721 --> 14:09.515
I'm Ben, Number Two.

14:09.598 --> 14:12.852
It is so good
to see you again, buddy. [chuckles]

14:12.935 --> 14:16.146
Why does everyone
keep looking at me like that?

14:16.689 --> 14:19.024
Because you've been dead for 15 years.

14:19.608 --> 14:20.651
[Ben] Dead?

14:20.734 --> 14:22.403
What do you mean, dead?

14:25.990 --> 14:27.032
Kind of a long story.

14:27.116 --> 14:29.410
Anyway, I'm Fei, Number Three.

14:29.493 --> 14:31.745
Alphonso, cuatro.

14:31.829 --> 14:33.581
Sloane. Five. Hey.

14:34.081 --> 14:36.208
-Hey.
-I'm Jayme, Six.

14:36.292 --> 14:38.752
[Ben] That's Christopher, of course.
Number Seven.

14:38.836 --> 14:39.837
[Christopher speaks]

14:39.920 --> 14:43.257
Oh, don't mind him.
He's in a bit of a saucy mood today.

14:43.340 --> 14:45.050
[Sparrows chuckling]

14:45.134 --> 14:46.260
He wouldn't get it.

14:46.343 --> 14:47.469
It's just so-- [laughs]

14:48.178 --> 14:50.014
[laughs]

14:50.097 --> 14:52.516
Wait, uh, what about, um, Number One?

14:52.600 --> 14:54.768
-What about him?
-Where is he?

14:54.852 --> 14:57.062
-[gasps]
-That's what we'd like to know.

15:02.985 --> 15:04.069
Are we playing a game?

15:04.653 --> 15:07.489
Whatever game the Umbrellas are playing,

15:07.573 --> 15:08.532
you're gonna lose!

15:09.950 --> 15:11.368
You took our Number One,

15:12.703 --> 15:13.913
so we took you.

15:13.996 --> 15:15.331
Wait, we took Marcus?

15:15.956 --> 15:18.042
[chuckles] Why would we do that?

15:18.125 --> 15:19.710
Act of war? Death wish?

15:19.793 --> 15:21.921
The last time we saw him,
he was with your sister.

15:22.004 --> 15:24.131
-Which one?
-The little one with the big powers.

15:24.214 --> 15:26.842
-Vanya? Huh.
-[ominous music playing]

15:27.801 --> 15:30.137
Well, I gotta say,

15:30.220 --> 15:32.806
it does not sound like Vanya
to go and kidnap anybody.

15:32.890 --> 15:34.433
[chuckles] You know, having said that,

15:34.516 --> 15:36.936
I am usually the last to know
about these kinda things.

15:37.019 --> 15:39.980
You're their Number One.
Shouldn't you know everything?

15:40.064 --> 15:41.440
I know. You'd think so, Ben.

15:41.523 --> 15:43.984
Discipline has never really been
our strong suit.

15:44.068 --> 15:46.946
It's pretty much
a free-for-all over there. [chuckles]

15:47.571 --> 15:48.447
So, listen.

15:49.448 --> 15:50.991
This sounds like an easy fix.

15:51.575 --> 15:52.409
I'll head back.

15:52.493 --> 15:55.496
I mean, my family's probably
worried sick about me, to be honest.

15:55.579 --> 15:58.791
And if they have your guy,
I'll send him back without a scratch.

15:58.874 --> 16:00.751
All right? No harm, no foul.

16:01.919 --> 16:03.212
How's that sound?

16:03.295 --> 16:04.129
Good?

16:04.922 --> 16:06.006
Great.

16:06.966 --> 16:10.052
What's the rush?
Stick around till Marcus is back.

16:10.552 --> 16:15.683
[Christopher speaks menacingly]

16:15.766 --> 16:17.601
[Luther] My family will come for me.

16:18.852 --> 16:19.687
Wonderful.

16:19.770 --> 16:22.314
In the meantime, make yourself at home.

16:24.191 --> 16:25.484
Oh, and, uh…

16:27.152 --> 16:29.863
before I forget, if you try to escape,

16:29.947 --> 16:33.993
Fei's birds will peck your eyes out
and make a nest inside your skull.

16:34.868 --> 16:36.495
[chuckles]

16:37.204 --> 16:38.122
Cool.

16:42.835 --> 16:46.005
So, what do you like to do for fun?

17:00.853 --> 17:02.980
[Viktor] Hey, d'you get any sleep?

17:03.063 --> 17:04.356
[food tray rattles]

17:04.857 --> 17:06.483
Brought you some breakfast.

17:08.944 --> 17:10.112
I'm not hungry.

17:10.821 --> 17:13.991
Come on. You should really eat something.

17:14.074 --> 17:16.535
-This is all my fault.
-Stop. No.

17:16.618 --> 17:19.163
I knew something could go wrong
if we came back.

17:19.246 --> 17:21.081
I knew it, and I risked it anyway.

17:22.249 --> 17:25.544
I left Ray to be with Claire, and now…

17:26.336 --> 17:28.005
Now it's like she never existed.

17:31.425 --> 17:33.677
And I don't even have a picture of her.

17:38.182 --> 17:39.058
[sighs]

17:40.392 --> 17:41.894
There might be a way out of this.

17:45.355 --> 17:46.356
What do you mean?

17:46.440 --> 17:49.568
Five's briefcase.
I'm gonna try and get it back.

17:51.653 --> 17:52.488
How?

17:52.571 --> 17:55.199
I'm meeting Marcus again today.
We're gonna do a trade.

17:55.282 --> 17:56.617
"Again"?

17:56.700 --> 18:00.079
-Yeah, I went to see him last night, and--
-Alone? What were you thinking?

18:01.038 --> 18:02.456
I needed to do something.

18:03.290 --> 18:05.250
For you. For… For all of us.

18:07.961 --> 18:10.297
-[scoffs]
-What? What do you--

18:10.380 --> 18:12.091
If you think I'm not coming,
you're insane!

18:12.174 --> 18:15.260
If you think I don't want you there
with me, then you're even crazier.

18:18.388 --> 18:19.473
[soft chuckle]

18:22.643 --> 18:24.394
Just don't give up yet, okay?

18:28.315 --> 18:30.067
Since when are you the optimist?

18:31.151 --> 18:33.153
Making a few changes, I guess.

18:33.237 --> 18:34.363
The hair?

18:36.740 --> 18:38.575
It's a bit more than that, actually, but…

18:40.244 --> 18:41.662
I'll explain on the way.

18:43.163 --> 18:44.206
Okay.

18:46.416 --> 18:49.336
[slurping loudly]

18:49.419 --> 18:51.839
[playful instrumental music playing]

18:51.922 --> 18:53.298
[belching]

18:56.260 --> 18:57.719
Berlin, here we come.

18:59.096 --> 19:01.390
[briefcase whirs]

19:01.473 --> 19:02.808
[briefcase powers down]

19:02.891 --> 19:04.268
Uh…

19:04.351 --> 19:06.562
Come on, work, you stupid briefcase.

19:07.271 --> 19:11.066
[briefcase whirs, sputters]

19:12.234 --> 19:14.653
[sputtering]

19:15.946 --> 19:18.115
I'm ready to go!

19:20.409 --> 19:23.036
Mother! Cunt! Bitch!

19:23.579 --> 19:24.830
Fuck off!

19:24.913 --> 19:27.958
Why won't you fucking work,

19:28.041 --> 19:29.793
you little bitch!

19:29.877 --> 19:33.630
I need to get to Berlin!

19:33.714 --> 19:34.548
Fuck!

19:35.257 --> 19:37.718
["The Oogum Boogum Song"
by Brenton Wood playing]

19:40.220 --> 19:42.598
♪ Oogum, oogum, boogum, boogum ♪

19:42.681 --> 19:45.309
♪ Boogum now, baby
You're castin' your spell on… ♪

19:48.979 --> 19:50.981
This actually isn't so terrible.

19:52.065 --> 19:53.483
See? Told you.

19:53.567 --> 19:56.361
Come to think of it,
my whole life I've been under the gun.

19:56.445 --> 19:57.404
Missions for Dad,

19:57.487 --> 20:00.616
working for the Commission,
trying to survive the apocalypse.

20:00.699 --> 20:02.910
I was always looking around every corner,

20:02.993 --> 20:05.746
just waiting for the other shoe to drop.

20:05.829 --> 20:08.373
-It's nice to just breathe.
-Good for you, man.

20:08.457 --> 20:10.542
Retirement is suiting you.

20:10.626 --> 20:13.003
Oh! Uh… All right!

20:13.086 --> 20:16.840
So, I've circled all
the roadside attractions along the way.

20:16.924 --> 20:19.843
-I'm not sure we're gonna have time…
-We have the Brownsville Big Nickel.

20:19.927 --> 20:22.137
Oh, Ricky's Bakery has award-winning pies.

20:22.221 --> 20:24.932
-If you just let me explain…
-Or there's this Cow Henge.

20:25.015 --> 20:26.183
That's it-- Don't--

20:26.266 --> 20:28.310
Listen to me.
Just shut up for two seconds, okay?

20:28.393 --> 20:30.270
Just two seconds? All right?

20:31.897 --> 20:34.358
Okay, I'm all ears.

20:36.026 --> 20:40.030
We are going to Pennsylvania to find

20:41.073 --> 20:43.075
my birth mother. Yay!

20:43.158 --> 20:45.077
-Excuse me?
-I'm sorry, okay? I'm sorry.

20:45.160 --> 20:47.996
I just needed somebody
to come with me for emotional support.

20:48.080 --> 20:50.123
Oh, emotional support, like a Schnauzer?

20:50.207 --> 20:53.377
I knew you wouldn't come if I told you,
so what was I supposed to do?

20:53.460 --> 20:56.213
You're goddamn right
I wouldn't have come, Klaus. You know why?

20:56.296 --> 20:59.424
-Because I am supposed to be retired!
-I know!

20:59.508 --> 21:01.551
This was supposed to be
a carefree road trip.

21:01.635 --> 21:03.303
Well, it still can be, babe.

21:04.137 --> 21:05.806
[Five] Ball of Twine? Klaus, turn!

21:05.889 --> 21:08.016
-Ball of Twine! Turn!
-What? Five! Five!

21:08.100 --> 21:10.519
It is one of the best ones! Come on!

21:10.602 --> 21:13.689
-Five, we're gonna die! Whoo!
-I don't care! Let go!

21:13.772 --> 21:16.108
[Five] You know what?
No twine, no birth mother!

21:16.191 --> 21:17.651
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

21:17.734 --> 21:19.403
I didn't-- Well, I…

21:19.486 --> 21:22.489
Uh, I just…
I can't believe I never realized.

21:22.572 --> 21:23.573
Well, how would you?

21:23.657 --> 21:25.784
No, I know, I just--
I feel like such an asshole.

21:25.867 --> 21:29.413
Hey, just… shut up for two seconds?

21:32.708 --> 21:34.626
You couldn't have known 'cause,

21:35.961 --> 21:37.296
I mean, I didn't fully.

21:39.840 --> 21:41.174
Being with Sissy…

21:43.176 --> 21:46.638
I don't know. She… opened something in me.

21:49.474 --> 21:52.728
Showed me I'd never be free
hiding from who I really am.

21:56.690 --> 21:59.067
And after losing her, I realized…

22:02.195 --> 22:03.280
[sighs]

22:03.363 --> 22:05.615
I just can't live in that box anymore.

22:08.201 --> 22:09.077
I won't.

22:13.957 --> 22:16.209
[dramatic string music playing]

22:17.336 --> 22:19.171
You know, I always hated mirrors.

22:20.297 --> 22:23.216
I thought everybody felt
so strange in their skin.

22:26.887 --> 22:28.638
I guess that's not true, right?

22:31.850 --> 22:33.310
What do you see now?

22:41.360 --> 22:42.361
Me.

22:46.531 --> 22:47.532
Just me.

22:53.872 --> 22:55.832
Thank you for trusting me with this.

22:56.666 --> 22:58.710
You're family, Viktor.

22:59.795 --> 23:00.629
Okay?

23:01.338 --> 23:02.756
And there's nothing…

23:03.632 --> 23:05.717
nothing that would make me love you less.

23:17.562 --> 23:19.106
Come on.

23:24.861 --> 23:26.029
[Klaus] Yeah, you know.

23:26.947 --> 23:29.616
I don't know why,
but I thought it'd be a lot bigger.

23:29.699 --> 23:31.118
-[Five] Seems pretty big to me.
-Ehh.

23:31.201 --> 23:32.702
Here's the real question.

23:32.786 --> 23:35.872
How do you know
your birth mother is in Pennsylvania?

23:36.915 --> 23:41.211
Well, because I was on the ass end
of a two-week bender,

23:41.294 --> 23:42.963
and I can't tell you the exact date

23:43.046 --> 23:45.966
because we were boofing Xanax
and the whole business,

23:46.049 --> 23:48.176
but Amy Winehouse
was at the top of the charts.

23:48.260 --> 23:51.221
So that puts us somewhere, where?
In the mid to late aughts?

23:52.389 --> 23:56.059
[Klaus] I helped myself into Dad's office,
looking for the key to his safe

23:56.143 --> 23:58.937
'cause he had
Pogo lock up all the stealables.

23:59.938 --> 24:03.608
But instead, I found a treasure trove
of our family history

24:03.692 --> 24:06.027
told in expired check stubs.

24:08.280 --> 24:09.114
[shudders]

24:09.739 --> 24:11.408
[Klaus] Rachel Herschberger?

24:11.491 --> 24:14.536
[soft string music playing]

24:14.619 --> 24:17.664
[Klaus] I was too messed up
to, uh, do anything about it,

24:17.747 --> 24:18.957
too scared to look her up.

24:19.040 --> 24:20.750
But always in the back of my mind,

24:20.834 --> 24:23.795
I wondered why she sold me off
for three grand.

24:23.879 --> 24:27.257
I mean, come on,
she couldn't have held out for five? Six?

24:27.841 --> 24:29.301
You see anything about my mother?

24:29.384 --> 24:31.595
No. Sorry.

24:32.929 --> 24:34.973
-Why now?
-Well, duh.

24:35.056 --> 24:37.100
Dad disowns us. Grace isn't Grace.

24:37.184 --> 24:39.186
Ben's… gone.

24:39.269 --> 24:43.064
Now just felt like a good a time as any
to find out who I could've been

24:43.148 --> 24:45.775
if I didn't grow up in this stupid family.

24:45.859 --> 24:48.195
Well, can you really call
what we had a family?

24:48.278 --> 24:49.613
No. It's more like a--

24:49.696 --> 24:52.199
-Institute for Snarky Delinquents.
-[laughs]

24:52.282 --> 24:53.533
And not a good one at that.

24:53.617 --> 24:55.660
But what is family? What is it?

24:55.744 --> 24:59.581
It's like some kind of giant…
ball of twine

24:59.664 --> 25:01.500
that can never be untangled.

25:01.583 --> 25:05.253
A giant ball of obligation
I've been pushing uphill my entire life.

25:05.337 --> 25:07.255
[Klaus] And the older you get,
the bigger it gets.

25:07.339 --> 25:10.383
-And the more you try and untangle it…
-You watch it roll down the hill…

25:10.467 --> 25:12.427
[in unison] And what's the point?

25:12.928 --> 25:15.013
Hey, I'm glad you came along.

25:17.015 --> 25:19.142
You're a good brother.

25:22.604 --> 25:25.190
All right, all right.
You say nice things about me now.

25:27.901 --> 25:29.611
Let's go find your stupid mother.

25:29.694 --> 25:31.821
[whimsical string music swells]

25:31.905 --> 25:33.740
Love you too, tiny dancer!

25:34.449 --> 25:36.952
[Diego] Hurry up. All right?
We gotta get back to the hotel.

25:37.035 --> 25:38.578
[Stan] Yeah, I gotta find the right one.

25:38.662 --> 25:41.164
-Just get the no-name shit.
-Have you tried the no-name shit?

25:41.248 --> 25:44.376
No, because ears don't squirt juice
every time I get excited.

25:44.459 --> 25:46.545
Yeah, then trust me. I need my brand.

25:48.922 --> 25:50.215
[entrance bell chimes]

25:50.298 --> 25:51.883
[Alphonso] Jayme, get me munchies.

25:53.885 --> 25:56.388
-Oh, I found it--
-[shushes]

25:56.471 --> 25:57.806
-Go wait outside.
-[Stan] Why?

25:57.889 --> 25:59.766
[Diego] I'm about to kick this fool's ass.

26:01.226 --> 26:03.603
-Don't worry. I got your back.
-Go.

26:03.687 --> 26:07.232
[suspenseful music playing]

26:11.278 --> 26:12.153
[sniffs]

26:13.572 --> 26:14.656
[sniffs]

26:14.739 --> 26:15.574
[Jayme humming]

26:20.537 --> 26:21.830
[clerk clears throat]

26:22.914 --> 26:24.416
[hisses]

26:37.721 --> 26:38.680
[sniffs]

26:40.682 --> 26:41.891
[Diego whistles]

26:49.190 --> 26:50.775
Well, isn't this a coinkidink?

26:50.859 --> 26:53.028
Only dink I see is yours, tough guy.

26:56.990 --> 26:58.867
-You followed me here?
-Don't flatter yourself.

26:58.950 --> 27:03.246
Leave now, or I'm gonna spank you
like the little bitch you are.

27:03.330 --> 27:05.040
["Quando Quando Quando" playing]

27:05.123 --> 27:06.750
Take your best shot, tubby.

27:10.795 --> 27:12.339
-[bone cracks]
-Oh shit!

27:12.422 --> 27:15.050
I know. Doesn't feel good, does it?

27:16.968 --> 27:20.972
♪ Tell me quando, quando, quando ♪

27:22.474 --> 27:25.352
♪ We can share a love divine ♪

27:25.435 --> 27:26.728
[grunts]

27:27.812 --> 27:31.816
♪ Please don't make me wait again ♪

27:36.780 --> 27:38.782
[Diego groans]

27:40.283 --> 27:41.368
[sharp exhale]

27:43.119 --> 27:45.163
♪ When will you say yes to me? ♪

27:45.246 --> 27:46.414
Ah shit!

27:48.667 --> 27:52.837
♪ Tell me quando, quando, quando ♪

27:52.921 --> 27:53.963
[bone snaps]

27:54.047 --> 27:56.841
-♪ You mean happiness to me ♪
-[grunts]

27:59.302 --> 28:02.639
♪ Oh, my love please tell me when ♪

28:05.225 --> 28:06.768
[panting]

28:07.644 --> 28:08.603
Dude, your chin.

28:11.064 --> 28:12.524
It does that sometimes.

28:23.159 --> 28:24.244
[groans]

28:25.412 --> 28:26.830
Stanley, no!

28:27.455 --> 28:28.790
[Stan groans]

28:29.374 --> 28:30.875
Goddamnit!

28:30.959 --> 28:32.502
Ow, my leg!

28:32.585 --> 28:35.880
-You getting how this works yet?
-That's my kid, asshole!

28:35.964 --> 28:36.798
[Alphonso groans]

28:39.342 --> 28:41.553
Are you getting tired yet?
Heart's getting weaker?

28:41.636 --> 28:43.847
Not… even close.

28:45.306 --> 28:46.558
[Alphonso snarls]

28:49.144 --> 28:51.104
[panting]

28:51.187 --> 28:53.857
-You all right? Where'd he get you?
-I'm fine. I'm fine!

28:53.940 --> 28:55.608
-[Diego] Oh, you'll be all right.
-Oh dear!

28:59.988 --> 29:03.950
You're good. You're okay.
It's not that bad. Stop crying, all right?

29:05.243 --> 29:07.245
[hissing]

29:10.540 --> 29:15.795
♪ To a joy beyond compare ♪

29:15.879 --> 29:17.756
♪ I can't wait a moment more… ♪

29:17.839 --> 29:19.007
[Stan] Watch out!

29:20.675 --> 29:22.427
That girl was gonna hork on you, dude.

29:22.510 --> 29:23.845
-[hisses]
-[Diego] Move! Get down!

29:25.096 --> 29:26.389
[groans]

29:26.473 --> 29:29.559
-I can handle my own shit!
-Yeah, sure you can. [grunts]

29:29.642 --> 29:31.144
[chuckles]

29:31.227 --> 29:32.604
[Diego grunts angrily]

29:33.897 --> 29:35.940
-Fuck yeah!
-Hey, watch your mouth!

29:36.608 --> 29:37.776
[Jayme groans]

29:39.319 --> 29:41.112
[groans]

29:42.655 --> 29:43.740
[Alphonso whimpers]

29:44.574 --> 29:45.700
Come on.

29:45.784 --> 29:48.119
[grunts] What? No way!
We were kicking their asses!

29:48.203 --> 29:51.039
"He who fights and walks away
lives to fight another day." Okay?

29:51.122 --> 29:52.707
-That's some lame-ass shit.
-Yeah, I know.

29:52.791 --> 29:53.875
♪ When? ♪

30:11.392 --> 30:13.686
Son of a bitch! Klaus is Amish.

30:13.770 --> 30:15.814
-This explains everything.
-[cows mooing]

30:15.897 --> 30:18.233
-How does this explain anything?
-Because look!

30:18.316 --> 30:19.567
Look at this place!

30:20.568 --> 30:22.403
This is everything
my childhood was missing.

30:22.487 --> 30:24.072
-Hey, uh, Klaus?
-[Klaus] Yeah?

30:24.155 --> 30:25.448
Wait up a minute.

30:25.532 --> 30:27.659
Doppelgänger check.
You feel anything strange?

30:27.742 --> 30:31.162
Uh, itching, sweats,
gas, anything like that?

30:31.246 --> 30:33.206
No. No, I feel great.

30:33.289 --> 30:37.460
Apart from the old rash on the tackle,
but what can you do?

30:38.211 --> 30:39.879
All right, good luck.

30:40.588 --> 30:42.715
What? Wait, you're not coming?

30:43.383 --> 30:45.301
-This one you gotta do alone.
-[Klaus sighs]

30:45.385 --> 30:46.469
Alone?

30:46.970 --> 30:48.054
Yeah, okay.

30:48.930 --> 30:50.473
Yeah, I can do that, sure.

30:50.557 --> 30:54.269
[pensive instrumental music playing]

30:54.978 --> 30:56.312
Hello there.

30:57.564 --> 30:59.858
[Klaus] Yoo-hoo! Guten haben.

31:16.291 --> 31:17.375
-Mom.
-[gasps]

31:20.128 --> 31:21.296
Nay, English.

31:22.171 --> 31:23.423
No mothers here.

31:24.716 --> 31:25.758
Only rabbits.

31:25.842 --> 31:27.385
Oh, I'm so sorry.

31:27.927 --> 31:30.471
I… I'm looking for Rachel Herschberger.

31:31.848 --> 31:33.057
[man] No Rachel.

31:33.141 --> 31:35.018
[Klaus] Oh, okay.

31:35.101 --> 31:37.145
Well, that's a shame.

31:37.228 --> 31:38.980
Do you happen to know
where I might find her?

31:39.063 --> 31:41.608
-I'm trying to track her down.
-[man] There's no Rachel here.

31:41.691 --> 31:45.445
Now, walk your fancy boots back to town
where you belong, and leave us be.

31:45.528 --> 31:46.738
Okay. [chuckles]

31:46.821 --> 31:49.407
All right. No need
to get your knickers in a twist there.

31:49.490 --> 31:50.867
[woman] Caleb, let the boy speak.

31:50.950 --> 31:53.703
You're upsetting the womenfolk,
and now you're upsetting me.

31:53.786 --> 31:54.996
No, that's not--

31:55.079 --> 31:57.332
I'm not upsetting the womenfolk.
Are you kidding?

31:57.415 --> 31:58.750
Womenfolk love me.

31:58.833 --> 32:00.084
[Caleb grunts]

32:00.168 --> 32:02.962
Ow! Jesus Christ!
What's the matter with you?

32:03.046 --> 32:06.174
I… I thought you people
were supposed to be nice!

32:06.257 --> 32:09.177
[Caleb] That's what you call
a misconception, English.

32:09.260 --> 32:10.219
All right, fine.

32:10.970 --> 32:12.221
Fine!

32:12.931 --> 32:14.140
But I want you to know

32:14.724 --> 32:17.727
that you have ruined
the Amish for me, forever!

32:17.810 --> 32:18.978
In here.

32:19.604 --> 32:20.563
Ruined!

32:23.274 --> 32:25.777
[Caleb] It's okay, Sarah-Beth.
He's leaving.

32:26.486 --> 32:28.905
[upbeat instrumental music playing]

32:33.785 --> 32:35.328
This place is incredible!

32:35.411 --> 32:37.956
We had the old lounge taken out
and had this put in.

32:38.039 --> 32:41.501
You know, I thought the home theater
and the Zen garden were impressive,

32:41.584 --> 32:43.211
but this is just next-level!

32:44.712 --> 32:45.672
You know,

32:46.589 --> 32:49.425
I always wanted the Umbrella Academy
to be like this.

32:49.509 --> 32:51.636
You guys actually do stuff together!

32:51.719 --> 32:52.679
You don't?

32:53.346 --> 32:54.305
Uh…

32:55.306 --> 32:56.474
Nah, not really.

32:56.557 --> 32:58.559
So, our brother died

32:59.852 --> 33:00.895
when we were kids.

33:00.979 --> 33:02.105
Number Six. Our Ben.

33:02.188 --> 33:03.189
Oh, I'm so sorry.

33:03.272 --> 33:05.900
Yeah, and after that,
nobody really gave a shit.

33:05.984 --> 33:07.735
Everyone had their own agenda,

33:07.819 --> 33:10.363
and it's like pulling teeth
to get anybody to actually care.

33:11.030 --> 33:15.702
And then, I guess after a while,
I stopped caring myself.

33:15.785 --> 33:17.704
You know, about training, the missions…

33:18.871 --> 33:22.291
About… being Number One. [scoffs]

33:23.501 --> 33:25.545
You're not what I was expecting.

33:26.212 --> 33:28.006
-I'm not?
-No.

33:28.089 --> 33:29.841
You're actually really sweet.

33:29.924 --> 33:32.051
[gentle piano music playing]

33:32.135 --> 33:33.177
[soft exhale]

33:38.266 --> 33:41.019
If I could,
I'd get out of here in a heartbeat.

33:41.769 --> 33:42.645
Why can't you?

33:43.688 --> 33:45.064
Why couldn't you?

33:45.148 --> 33:46.149
Fair point.

33:46.858 --> 33:50.111
This house,
it's all I've ever known my entire life.

33:51.154 --> 33:53.573
And I know there are better places
out there in the world,

33:53.656 --> 33:56.534
and one day, I want to see them all.

33:57.827 --> 33:58.995
You know, I, uh…

34:00.997 --> 34:02.874
I spent a little time on the moon.

34:02.957 --> 34:05.334
What? That is so cool!

34:06.878 --> 34:09.964
-You think so?
-Yeah! The moon?

34:10.048 --> 34:12.133
-My God. No one ever thinks that's cool.
-Yes!

34:12.216 --> 34:13.760
[both laughing]

34:13.843 --> 34:15.428
The moon, yeah!

34:24.312 --> 34:25.229
[soft gasp]

34:26.439 --> 34:29.317
So, tell me a little bit more
about that family of yours

34:29.400 --> 34:31.402
before they decide to come and rescue you.

34:31.486 --> 34:33.362
Where are you guys staying anyway?

34:33.446 --> 34:35.823
Oh, just some dumpy hotel downtown.

34:35.907 --> 34:36.783
Uh, the Hotel--

34:39.452 --> 34:41.662
-You're trying to honey trap me.
-No, no, no.

34:41.746 --> 34:44.665
No, of course. Luther, you're so stupid!

34:44.749 --> 34:46.417
Oh, wow!
You really think the moon is cool?

34:46.501 --> 34:47.919
-Luther, I wasn't--
-Duh!

34:48.002 --> 34:49.003
-I'm such--
-[raven caws]

34:50.797 --> 34:52.131
Ben would like a word.

34:53.132 --> 34:54.217
Go get cleaned up.

34:56.177 --> 34:58.137
-Luther, I wasn't trying---
-Sloane.

35:01.641 --> 35:04.352
[ominous music playing]

35:13.069 --> 35:15.822
[ominous music swells]

35:19.867 --> 35:22.245
[shockwave pulsing]

35:22.328 --> 35:25.623
[country song plays on radio]
♪ Well, it's a cryin' shame ♪

35:26.541 --> 35:28.709
[singing along]
♪ You don't even know my name ♪

35:28.793 --> 35:30.128
[energy pulsing]

35:30.211 --> 35:32.463
-♪ But every time you pass me by ♪
-[mooing]

35:32.547 --> 35:34.549
♪ Girl, it makes me wanna cry ♪

35:34.632 --> 35:37.552
-♪ It's a cryin' shame ♪
-[distressed mooing]

35:38.136 --> 35:39.720
♪ I go inside the-- ♪

35:41.347 --> 35:42.306
What is…?

35:47.061 --> 35:49.647
Oh, can't I get one fucking day off?

36:00.032 --> 36:02.535
I wasn't sure what kind you like best.

36:03.995 --> 36:05.621
You did create all of them.

36:06.539 --> 36:08.166
[energy thrumming]

36:22.805 --> 36:24.849
[thrumming loudly]

36:24.932 --> 36:29.270
[Grace breathes heavily]

36:30.855 --> 36:32.064
[Grace exhales sharply]

36:40.031 --> 36:41.949
-Hey!
-[Sarah-Beth screams]

36:42.033 --> 36:43.117
Sorry! Sorry, sorry, sorry.

36:43.201 --> 36:45.036
-I don't want any trouble.
-No, no!

36:45.119 --> 36:46.454
Hey.

36:46.537 --> 36:49.207
You know Rachel, don't you?

36:49.290 --> 36:50.333
She's my sister.

36:50.416 --> 36:51.876
Oh!

36:51.959 --> 36:52.877
[laughs]

36:52.960 --> 36:54.086
Hey! [chuckles]

36:55.296 --> 36:58.090
So, where can I find her?

36:58.174 --> 37:01.177
Young man, she's been dead
for over 30 years.

37:01.260 --> 37:03.304
-Oh.
-[soft piano music playing]

37:03.387 --> 37:06.307
So, but… how did she die?

37:06.390 --> 37:07.725
Brain hemorrhage.

37:08.476 --> 37:09.936
Took her quick, thank the Lord.

37:10.019 --> 37:10.978
What about her son?

37:11.062 --> 37:12.021
What son?

37:12.813 --> 37:15.274
Wait. When did she die again?

37:15.358 --> 37:17.151
She passed October 1st,

37:18.152 --> 37:19.153
1989.

37:20.571 --> 37:21.489
Oh.

37:23.491 --> 37:26.202
-What's the matter?
-No, it's just that that's my…

37:27.662 --> 37:28.913
That's my birthday.

37:29.956 --> 37:32.500
-[Caleb] English, the cows are missing!
-You need to leave. Now.

37:32.583 --> 37:34.043
-Oh! Oh shit!
-Go now!

37:35.336 --> 37:37.463
[ticking loudly]

37:37.546 --> 37:40.675
[distorted chatter in background]

37:40.758 --> 37:43.302
[distorted laughter]

37:43.928 --> 37:45.221
[laughing]

37:46.514 --> 37:47.640
[screaming]

37:48.266 --> 37:49.183
Listen.

37:50.309 --> 37:52.937
You know how to use this briefcase, right?

37:53.020 --> 37:55.273
Because last time Klaus tried it,
he ended up in Vietnam,

37:55.356 --> 37:57.942
and I can't handle another screwup,
Viktor, I swear to God, I can't.

37:58.025 --> 37:59.610
I know, I know.

38:00.361 --> 38:01.404
Me neither.

38:03.656 --> 38:05.283
Hey, Five is an asshole…

38:05.366 --> 38:06.200
Yes.

38:06.284 --> 38:07.952
…but he's not a monster.

38:09.578 --> 38:11.956
When we explain
what this means to us, he'll help.

38:12.039 --> 38:13.165
He has to.

38:15.668 --> 38:17.545
But first, we need to get that briefcase.

38:19.380 --> 38:20.631
[bell jingles]

38:22.800 --> 38:23.801
[man] Here you go.

38:25.094 --> 38:28.097
-[Klaus] Five! Five!
-[playful instrumental music playing]

38:28.180 --> 38:30.057
Start the car, would ya?

38:31.058 --> 38:32.727
-[Amish clamoring]
-Oh my…

38:32.810 --> 38:35.271
Shit, shit, shit! Five!

38:36.605 --> 38:38.316
Start the car!

38:38.399 --> 38:40.318
Five! Start the car!

38:40.401 --> 38:42.611
Hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry!

38:42.695 --> 38:46.741
-Why can't you just get along with people?
-I tried. Really, I did. I tried!

38:46.824 --> 38:49.285
-Wait, wait, wait!
-Hold on a second!

38:49.368 --> 38:50.745
-Take this.
-What is it?

38:50.828 --> 38:53.539
Rachel's death was unusual,
and she wasn't the only one.

38:53.622 --> 38:55.541
Come on! Get in the car, Klaus!

38:55.624 --> 38:56.876
You have her eyes.

38:56.959 --> 38:59.503
-English, go!
-[Five] Klaus, it's now or never!

38:59.587 --> 39:00.504
Klaus!

39:00.588 --> 39:02.381
Go, go!

39:02.465 --> 39:04.467
[car engine starts]

39:04.550 --> 39:07.303
[Amish yelling and clamoring]

39:07.386 --> 39:09.722
This whole timeline's
chock-full of riddles. Get this.

39:09.805 --> 39:12.850
My mom died here before I was even born!

39:12.933 --> 39:14.602
[brakes screeching]

39:15.227 --> 39:16.979
-What did you just say?
-Yeah.

39:20.483 --> 39:21.942
[bell jingles]

39:24.403 --> 39:25.780
He's not gonna show.

39:25.863 --> 39:27.615
Something must be wrong.

39:27.698 --> 39:29.658
Or he's blowing you off.

39:29.742 --> 39:31.077
He's not the type.

39:31.160 --> 39:33.746
And you know that
after spending 15 minutes together?

39:38.125 --> 39:41.587
[ominous music playing]

39:41.670 --> 39:43.714
[in Southern accent]
We don't let your kind in here.

39:43.798 --> 39:44.924
What did you say?

39:49.345 --> 39:51.430
[server] I said you're still here.

39:51.514 --> 39:54.016
Do you wanna order
while you're waiting for your friend?

39:54.100 --> 39:55.142
-Yeah.
-No, that--

39:55.226 --> 39:57.353
-[baby crying]
-I'll be back. No rush.

39:57.895 --> 39:59.688
-Allison, are you okay?
-[Allison] I… I…

40:01.482 --> 40:02.983
I don't-- [sniffles]

40:03.567 --> 40:04.985
[Claire] One more story, Mommy.

40:05.069 --> 40:06.404
Claire, honey.

40:06.487 --> 40:08.280
-[rapid breaths]
-[Claire] Mom, I want a story!

40:08.364 --> 40:10.616
[voice echoes]
I heard a rumor that you're really tired.

40:10.699 --> 40:13.285
-[screaming]
-Allison, come on. What is happening?

40:13.369 --> 40:14.495
Where is Claire?!

40:14.578 --> 40:16.372
-I need to get some air.
-Hey!

40:16.455 --> 40:17.498
Where are you g--?

40:19.333 --> 40:21.335
[panting]

40:24.672 --> 40:26.048
[Allison] What are you looking at?

40:33.431 --> 40:34.306
[Allison] Hey!

40:41.856 --> 40:43.357
[Allison] Hey, I'm talking to you!

41:04.587 --> 41:06.255
[urine trickling]

41:06.338 --> 41:07.548
[bottles clinking]

41:08.507 --> 41:09.592
Oh!

41:09.675 --> 41:10.551
Sorry.

41:10.634 --> 41:13.012
[murmuring]

41:15.181 --> 41:16.223
[Viktor] Allison?

41:18.225 --> 41:19.310
Are you okay?

41:19.393 --> 41:20.978
[wheels of cart squeaking]

41:21.937 --> 41:22.813
[Allison] Yeah.

41:23.397 --> 41:24.440
Um…

41:27.485 --> 41:28.360
Let's go.

41:40.331 --> 41:43.209
[wind howling]

41:47.671 --> 41:49.798
[Jayme] You were basically
screaming for help.

41:49.882 --> 41:51.884
[Alphonso] I wasn't screaming.
I was kicking his ass.

41:51.967 --> 41:53.344
You couldn't breathe, but…

41:53.427 --> 41:55.804
Doesn't look like
your family is coming anytime soon.

41:55.888 --> 41:57.890
Oh, no, I'm sure they're just,

41:57.973 --> 42:00.184
you know, working out
the final details and…

42:00.267 --> 42:01.602
-[floorboards creak]
-…such.

42:04.188 --> 42:06.273
Relax. You're free to go.

42:06.357 --> 42:07.191
Why?

42:07.775 --> 42:09.026
Gesture of goodwill.

42:09.109 --> 42:12.488
But I want you to pass along
a very important message to your family.

42:12.571 --> 42:13.572
Yeah, of course.

42:15.449 --> 42:16.784
Let Marcus go.

42:16.867 --> 42:20.996
And if any of you hurt one hair on him,
we'll come for you.

42:21.080 --> 42:23.332
-[Ben] All of you.
-[ominous music playing]

42:23.415 --> 42:26.544
And I promise
we won't be so hospitable next time.

42:28.045 --> 42:30.047
Super don't like being threatened, Ben.

42:30.130 --> 42:32.132
You'll do as we say, or else…

42:32.633 --> 42:34.134
[ravens screeching]

42:34.218 --> 42:36.303
Birds. In my brain.

42:36.387 --> 42:38.013
-[raven caws]
-Got it.

42:38.097 --> 42:40.224
Don't forget your tote bag.
[snaps fingers]

42:47.189 --> 42:48.983
Hope you enjoyed your stay.

42:49.567 --> 42:50.901
[raven caws]

43:22.600 --> 43:23.601
[raven caws]

43:23.684 --> 43:24.893
[wings fluttering]

43:29.356 --> 43:30.733
[raven screeches]

43:31.942 --> 43:32.943
[gasps]

43:33.027 --> 43:34.778
[laughs softly]

43:35.487 --> 43:38.365
[laughing] Oh!

43:38.449 --> 43:39.450
Excuse me.

43:39.533 --> 43:41.952
I mean, who does that? Who does it?

43:42.036 --> 43:43.621
[jazz piano playing in background]

43:43.704 --> 43:46.206
What are you mumbling about?

43:46.290 --> 43:47.166
Lila.

43:47.833 --> 43:49.710
Dumping Stan on me after all these years?

43:49.793 --> 43:51.629
-I mean, that's not right.
-[scoffs]

43:51.712 --> 43:54.381
Hey, man. If you did the deed,
don't blame her for the consequences.

43:54.465 --> 43:55.424
That's not the point.

43:55.507 --> 43:56.675
Oh, what's the point?

43:57.259 --> 43:58.844
He's cramping my style.

43:59.428 --> 44:03.557
I need to be able to react to danger
on a moment's notice.

44:03.641 --> 44:06.602
How am I to do that when I'm playing
wet nurse to a 12-year-old?

44:06.685 --> 44:08.520
You're his dad!

44:08.604 --> 44:10.314
Alleged dad.

44:12.232 --> 44:14.026
Well, at least you have a kid.

44:18.489 --> 44:20.199
[Allison] Can I get another one?

44:25.037 --> 44:27.206
[Five] Okay, gather round, people.

44:27.873 --> 44:30.000
Where is-- Where's every-- Where's Luther?

44:30.084 --> 44:31.418
-Haven't seen him.
-Who knows?

44:31.502 --> 44:33.462
Anybody know where-- Okay, you know what?

44:33.545 --> 44:35.673
We got bigger problems
to worry about right now.

44:35.756 --> 44:36.757
Like what?

44:38.926 --> 44:40.302
This.

44:40.386 --> 44:42.346
[suspenseful orchestral music playing]

44:42.429 --> 44:43.639
[Viktor] Who are they?

44:43.722 --> 44:45.683
[Five] These are our mothers.

44:49.061 --> 44:50.062
That one's mine.

44:52.189 --> 44:53.273
They're all dead.

44:53.816 --> 44:56.110
They all died on the exact same day,

44:56.193 --> 44:57.986
October 1st, 1989.

44:58.070 --> 45:00.197
-[Viktor] That's our birthday.
-Not anymore, it isn't.

45:00.280 --> 45:01.782
They all died before we were born.

45:01.865 --> 45:04.743
That's dumb.
If we weren't born, how can we exist?

45:04.827 --> 45:06.870
-Exactly.
-What are you saying?

45:07.621 --> 45:11.208
I'm saying, when we jumped here,
we created a time paradox.

45:11.291 --> 45:13.419
All right? Not just any paradox.

45:13.502 --> 45:16.171
This is the grandfather paradox.

45:16.255 --> 45:18.465
What the hell is a grandfather paradox?

45:25.514 --> 45:28.892
[distant police siren wailing]

45:34.857 --> 45:36.066
[Sloane] Psst!

45:36.150 --> 45:38.110
[whispering] Luther! Hey!

45:38.777 --> 45:41.488
["Higher Love" by Lilly Winwood playing]
♪ Think about it ♪

45:42.281 --> 45:45.117
♪ There must be a higher love ♪

45:45.993 --> 45:50.205
♪ Down in the heart
Or in the stars above ♪

45:50.831 --> 45:52.583
♪ Without it ♪

45:53.167 --> 45:55.878
-[Luther] Whoa! What the…
-♪ Life is wasted time ♪

45:56.628 --> 45:58.714
♪ Look inside your heart ♪

45:58.797 --> 46:01.675
♪ I'll look inside of mine ♪

46:02.634 --> 46:05.804
♪ Things look so bad everywhere ♪

46:05.888 --> 46:06.889
[thud]

46:08.223 --> 46:10.517
♪ In this whole world ♪

46:10.601 --> 46:11.685
♪ What's fair? ♪

46:11.769 --> 46:13.228
Go get 'em, T. J. [crunching]

46:13.312 --> 46:16.857
♪ We walk blind and we try to see ♪

46:19.193 --> 46:22.863
♪ Falling behind in what could be ♪

46:24.656 --> 46:27.659
♪ Bring me a higher love… ♪

46:29.244 --> 46:30.329
Hey.

46:30.412 --> 46:31.663
-Shit.
-[Sloane] Oh…

46:31.747 --> 46:34.208
-Okay, now what?
-Here. Yes.

46:34.792 --> 46:35.918
[window creaking]

46:36.001 --> 46:37.795
Just need to… [grunts]

46:37.878 --> 46:39.546
Just… Yeah. Okay.

46:39.630 --> 46:42.090
[Sloane] Um, I'm gonna take this from you.

46:43.509 --> 46:44.635
We have to be quiet.

46:44.718 --> 46:47.012
[sighs] What the hell do you want from me?

46:47.095 --> 46:51.058
I wanted to apologize for earlier.

46:51.141 --> 46:52.851
Is this another one of your games?

46:52.935 --> 46:54.353
No, you don't understand.

46:54.436 --> 46:55.854
We were being watched.

46:55.938 --> 46:56.897
What? By who?

46:56.980 --> 46:59.149
My family. They're crazy.

46:59.233 --> 47:03.487
But I want to let you know,
I meant every word I said.

47:04.154 --> 47:05.697
Even about the moon?

47:05.781 --> 47:07.783
Especially about the moon.

47:11.495 --> 47:12.579
Well, um…

47:15.916 --> 47:17.376
Is anyone watching us now?

47:17.960 --> 47:20.212
No. But I mean, we should be--

47:20.295 --> 47:23.465
♪ We walk blind and we try to see ♪

47:25.300 --> 47:28.428
♪ Falling behind in what could be ♪

47:30.931 --> 47:33.809
♪ Bring me a higher love ♪

47:36.478 --> 47:40.190
♪ Bring me a higher love ♪

47:41.984 --> 47:44.862
♪ Bring me a higher love ♪

47:46.405 --> 47:49.074
♪ Where's this higher love ♪

47:49.157 --> 47:51.702
♪ I've been thinking of? ♪

47:52.995 --> 47:56.331
♪ I will wait for it ♪

47:58.834 --> 48:03.130
♪ I'm not too late for it ♪

48:03.922 --> 48:08.343
♪ Until then, I'll sing my song… ♪

48:08.427 --> 48:12.347
[rock violin music playing]
